This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with crowd counting in images and videos. The use of deep learning models such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and convolutional LSTM (ConvLSTM) also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of transfer learning, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of regression models, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of bidirectional ConvLSTM models suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
